                                "text": "Add forward.\n\nthis builds the following:\n\n{\n    \"0\": [1 ],\n    \"1\": [0, 2 ],\n    \"2\": [1, 3, 5],\n    \"3\": [2, 4],\n    \"4\": [3 ],\n    \"5\": [2, 6],\n    \"6\": [5 ]\n}\n\nFor connections, we walk (from a key numer) in a direction, generating pairs.\nSome keys will fork - but that should generated the connected pair set.\n\ne.g, pulling '3',\n\n    3 -> 2, 4\n            4 -> [3]      <= not executed,\n         2 -> 1, [3], 5   <= skip 3, as \"2\"\n              1 -> 0, 2   <= skip 2, as \"1\"\n                     ...",
